
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "ViewDiseases";
}


    <div class="jumbotron container">
        <form class="form-inline my-2 my-lg-0">
            <input class="form-control mr-sm-2" type="text" placeholder="Search">
            <button class="btn btn-secondary my-2 my-sm-0" type="submit">Search</button>
        </form>
        <br />
        <div class="card-columns">

            <div class="card border-primary mb-3" alt="">
                <div class="card-header">Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease</div>

                <div class="card-body">

                    <p class="card-text">
                        As a disease group in which airflow obstruction is observed due to chronic bronchitis or emphysema, airflow obstruction is mostly irreversible and progressive.

                    </p>

                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card border-primary mb-3" alt="">
                <div class="card-header">Occupational Asthma</div>

                <div class="card-body">

                    <p class="card-text">
                        Occupational asthma is defined as asthma caused by exposure to agents
                        encountered in the working environment in workers without pre-existing
                        asthma. Airways responsiveness is obstruction in nature and results in
                        wheeze, chest tightness, cough and shortness of breath
                    </p>

                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card border-primary mb-3" alt="">
                <div class="card-header">Malignant mesothelioma</div>

                <div class="card-body">

                    <p class="card-text">Malignant mesothelioma is a malignant tumor arising from mesothelial cells. It mainly occurs on the pleura and is known as a pleural tumor. Among pleural tumors, exposure to asbestos is well known as the cause of malignant mesothelioma.In particular, it is known that about 70% of malignant mesothelioma in the pleura is caused by continuous inhalation of asbestos. </p>

                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card border-primary mb-3" alt="">
                <div class="card-header">Bronchiolitis obliterans</div>

                <div class="card-body">

                    <p class="card-text">It  is a respiratory disease caused by injury to the smallest airways. Inflammation of the bronchioles, which is the peripheral airway, refers to bronchitis in which airways are blocked.  </p>

                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card border-primary mb-3" alt="">
                <div class="card-header">Lung cancer</div>

                <div class="card-body">

                    <p class="card-text">
                        Lung cancer refers to malignant tumors in the lungs, and can be divided into primary lung cancer, in which cancer cells are formed in the tissues that make up the lungs, and metastatic lung cancer, in which cancer cells form in other organs and then move to the lungs and proliferate.
                    </p>

                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card border-primary mb-3" alt="">
                <div class="card-header">Hypersensitivity pneumonitis</div>

                <div class="card-body">

                    <p class="card-text">
                        It is a disease that causes immune inflammation along with granulomas in the lung parenchyma such as bronchioles and alveoli by introducing various antigens such as spores, spores of fungi, organic substances of animals and plants, chemical substances, and toxic gases through the airways.
                    </p>

                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card border-primary mb-3" alt="">
                <div class="card-header">Asbestosis</div>

                <div class="card-body">

                    <p class="card-text">Asbestosis begins with respiratory bronchiolitis and alveolitis, causes diffuse pulmonary fibrosis, and is followed by thickening and calcification of the parietal pleura. </p>

                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card border-primary mb-3" alt="">
                <div class="card-header">Pneumoconiosis</div>

                <div class="card-body">

                    <p class="card-text">Pneumoconiosis is one of a group of interstitial lung disease caused by breathing in certain kinds of dust particles that damage your lungs.One of the most common forms is black lung disease, also known as miner's lung. It’s caused by breathing in coal dust.    </p>

                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card border-primary mb-3" alt="">
                <div class="card-header">Silicosis</div>

                <div class="card-body">

                    <p class="card-text">When dust containing silicic acid accumulates in the lungs, the lungs become inflamed by the mechanical and chemical actions of silicic acid. This inflammation eventually leaves a scar on the lungs, and over time, eventually, the lungs cause problems in supplying oxygen to the whole body. </p>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>